Here’s a sample .gitignore file tailored for a FastAPI project. It includes common exclusions for Python, FastAPI, and related tools:
# Byte-compiled / optimized / DLL files
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class

# Virtual environment
env/
venv/
ENV/
.venv/

# FastAPI specific
instance/
*.db
*.sqlite3

# Logs
*.log
*.out
*.err
logs/

# IDEs and editors
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo

# Testing
.pytest_cache/
.coverage
.tox/
.nox/
.cache/

# OS generated files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Docker
*.dockerignore
docker-compose.override.yml

# Environment variables
.env
.env.*

# Build artifacts
build/
dist/
*.egg-info/

This .gitignore file ensures sensitive files, temporary files, and unnecessary directories are excluded from version control. You can customize it further based on your project's specific needs.
